article_title: 17.6 million have gained health coverage under the Affordable Care Act
article_text:
New marketplace enrollment figures show nation’s uninsured rate at all-time low

Hispanics and African Americans saw the greatest declines in their uninsured rates

HHS expects difficulty covering the remaining 10.5 million uninsured who are eligible for marketplace coverage

article_metadata.title: 17.6 million have gained health coverage under the Affordable Care Act | McClatchy DC

og.description: A new government report released Tuesday finds 17.6 million Americans have gained health insurance coverage since the Affordable Care Act became law in 2010.
